{
  "title": "PIDCAT for Android Bug Bounty Logging",
  "breadcrumb": [],
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "A focused logcat wrapper for Android security researchers and bug bounty hunters — helps filter logs from a specific app instead of the entire device, making vulnerability analysis faster and cleaner."
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "id": "why-use-pidcat",
      "content": "Why Use PIDCAT?"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "id": "adb-logcat-default-behavior",
      "content": "adb logcat (Default behavior)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "adb devices\nadb -s <device-ip:port> logcat"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Captures all logs from the device: system, apps, services.",
        "Noisy and difficult to isolate logs for one app."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "id": "pidcat-focused-behavior",
      "content": "pidcat (Focused behavior)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "pidcat -s <device-ip:port> <package.name>"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Captures logs only from a specific app using its PID (process ID).",
        "Automatically updates PID if the app restarts.",
        "Filters out irrelevant system logs."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "id": "installation",
      "content": "Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "id": "id-1.-clone-the-repository",
      "content": "1. Clone the Repository"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "git clone https://github.com/JakeWharton/pidcat.git\ncd pidcat"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "id": "id-2.-run-directly",
      "content": "2. Run Directly"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "On Linux/macOS:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "./pidcat.py -s <device-ip:port> <package.name>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "On Windows:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "python pidcat.py -s <device-ip:port> <package.name>"
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "id": "make-it-universal-on-windows",
      "content": "Make It Universal on Windows"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "To run pidcat from any directory:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ordered_list",
      "items": [
        "Move pidcat.py to a folder like C:\\Tools\\pidcat\\",
        "Add that folder to the System PATH:\n- Open Environment Variables\n- Edit the Path variable\n- Add: C:\\Tools\\pidcat",
        "(Optional) Create pidcat.bat in the same folder:\n\n@echo off\npython C:\\Tools\\pidcat\\pidcat.py %*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Now you can run:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code_block",
      "language": "bash",
      "content": "pidcat -s <device-ip:port> com.target.app"
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "id": "example-commands",
      "content": "Example Commands"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "For a remote device:",
          "code": "pidcat -s 192.168.0.101:5555 com.target.app"
        },
        {
          "title": "For a USB device:",
          "code": "pidcat com.target.app"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "id": "original-repository",
      "content": "Original Repository"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "https://github.com/JakeWharton/pidcat"
    }
  ],
